<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 7:25PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Washington County through 815 PM MDT...
At 724 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Apple Valley, or near Colorado City, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Apple Valley and Hildale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
